# Citation File Format (https://citation-file-format.github.io/) — lets GitHub
# render a "Cite this repository" widget and gives reusers a canonical reference.
cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "fyp-quant: A matched-pair framework for safety–capability trade-offs in quantized small language models"
message: "If you use this framework or its findings, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Tan"
    given-names: "Uei Horng"
    affiliation: "College of Computing and Data Science, Nanyang Technological University"
abstract: >-
  An open, reproducible benchmarking framework that evaluates safety–capability
  trade-offs in small instruction-tuned LLMs under quantization. It uses a
  matched-pair design (identical baseline weights, quantization applied on the
  fly) across three precisions (fp16, INT8/LLM.int8, NF4 four-bit) and four
  benchmarks (HarmBench, XSTest, MMLU, ARC-Challenge). HarmBench Attack Success
  Rate is scored by the official HarmBench classifier as the primary judge,
  cross-checked by a second (gpt-4o) judge; a capability-anchored interpretation
  layer distinguishes genuine alignment shifts from capability degradation.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - quantization
  - AI safety
  - evaluation framework
  - HarmBench
  - reproducibility
repository-code: "https://github.com/tanueihorng/llm-ethics-benchmark"
